+# PLAN.md — discord-mcp-oauth
+
+Living build plan. Updated after every chunk. If this file disagrees with the
+code, the code wins — flag and update it.
+
+## Goal
+
+A remote [Model Context Protocol](https://modelcontextprotocol.io) server
+that bridges Discord with any MCP-compatible client (Claude.ai, Claude Code,
+Cursor, Cline, Zed, `mcp-remote`) via **multi-user OAuth**, deployed to
+**Cloudflare Workers**.
+
+Differentiators vs. existing community Discord MCP servers:
+
+- Per-user OAuth, no shared hardcoded token.
+- Serverless; no Docker/VPS.
+- Streamable HTTP transport (SSE is deprecated).
+- Client-agnostic (registered via Dynamic Client Registration, RFC 7591).
+- Production-grade defaults; intended as a portfolio showcase.
+
+## Tech stack — locked in
+
+| Concern       | Choice                                                                                                                                           |
+| ------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
+| Language      | TypeScript, strict mode (`noUncheckedIndexedAccess`, `exactOptionalPropertyTypes`, `noPropertyAccessFromIndexSignature`, `verbatimModuleSyntax`) |
+| Runtime       | Cloudflare Workers                                                                                                                               |
+| MCP           | `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk` + custom Streamable HTTP adapter                                                                                     |
+| HTTP router   | Hono                                                                                                                                             |
+| Schemas       | Zod 4                                                                                                                                            |
+| Token storage | Durable Objects (one DO per Discord user)                                                                                                        |
+| MCP OAuth     | `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk` primitives wrapped in a Workers-native provider                                                                      |
+| Discord OAuth | Hand-rolled (50 LOC, no extra dep surface)                                                                                                       |
+| Discord API   | Typed REST client wrapper (no `discord.js` — it assumes a gateway connection Workers cannot hold)                                                |
+| Tests         | Vitest (node pool now; Workers pool added in chunk 3 for DO tests)                                                                               |
+| Deploy        | Wrangler                                                                                                                                         |
+| Lint/format   | ESLint 9 flat + typescript-eslint strict-type-checked, Prettier                                                                                  |
+
+## Design decisions — locked in
+
+1. **Discord auth model:** shared-bot + user-OAuth. Users grant `identify guilds`;
+   the bot token (Worker secret) performs data-plane calls. Authorization
+   guard: `guild_id ∈ user.GET /users/@me/guilds` before any guild-scoped
+   tool call. Bot must be invited to each target guild; error messages
+   surface a ready-to-click invite URL when absent.
+2. **Token storage:** Durable Objects, keyed by `discord_user_id`. Avoids
+   KV's lost-update race on concurrent refresh. Refresh is serialized inside
+   the DO; 60s skew window; rotated refresh tokens persisted atomically.
+3. **Region:** EU (`locationHint: "weur"`) by default for GDPR posture, with
+   a `WORKER_REGION` knob for forks.
+4. **MCP session model:** session-scoped, keyed by `Mcp-Session-Id`. A
+   lighter `SessionDO` maps `session_id → discord_user_id`. Session TTL 24h
+   sliding; Discord refresh token proactively rotated inside `UserTokenDO`
+   regardless of session activity.
+5. **Agent-agnostic:** no hardcoded client names or redirect URIs. DCR
+   drives everything. Consent page renders the registered `client_name`
+   dynamically. README ships quickstarts for multiple clients in
+   `docs/clients.md`.
+
+## MVP tool scope — locked in
+
+Each tool: Zod input schema, descriptive error mapping, `{ content: [...] }`
+response.
+
+| Tool                               | Purpose                                                |
+| ---------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------ |
+| `list_guilds`                      | Servers the authenticated user is a member of.         |
+| `list_channels`                    | Channels in a guild (text/forum/thread).               |
+| `send_message`                     | Post a message to a channel.                           |
+| `read_recent_messages`             | Last N (cap 100) messages from a channel.              |
+| `search_messages`                  | Query by text, author, date range; cap 100, paginated. |
+| `add_reaction` / `remove_reaction` | Manage reactions on a message.                         |
+| `create_thread`                    | From a message or standalone.                          |
+| `get_user_info`                    | Current authenticated Discord identity.                |
+
+**Out of scope (MVP):** role management, voice, webhook CRUD, slash command
+registration, forum post CRUD, DMs.
+
+**Bot permissions requested on invite:** `View Channels`, `Send Messages`,
+`Read Message History`, `Add Reactions`, `Create Public Threads`. No
+`Manage Messages`.
+
+## Module layout
+
+```
+src/
+├── index.ts                      # Worker fetch handler, router
+├── env.ts                        # Zod-validated env/bindings             [chunk 1]
+├── mcp/
+│   ├── server.ts                 # MCP Server + tool registration
+│   ├── transport.ts              # Streamable HTTP adapter
+│   └── errors.ts                 # MCP error helpers
+├── oauth/
+│   ├── mcp-provider.ts           # What the MCP client authenticates against
+│   ├── discord-client.ts         # Discord OAuth2: authorize, exchange, refresh, PKCE
+│   └── bridge.ts                 # MCP auth code ↔ Discord identity
+├── discord/
+│   ├── rest-client.ts            # Typed fetch wrapper, auth header, retry
+│   ├── rate-limiter.ts           # X-RateLimit-* + Retry-After bucket tracking
+│   ├── errors.ts                 # DiscordPermissionError, NotFound, RateLimit, …
+│   └── schemas.ts                # Zod schemas for Discord REST payloads
+├── tools/
+│   ├── registry.ts               # Binds all tools to the MCP server
+│   └── <one file per tool>
+├── authz/
+│   └── guild-membership.ts       # "user ∈ guild?" guard
+├── storage/
+│   ├── user-token-do.ts          # Per-user token state, serialized refresh
+│   ├── session-do.ts             # MCP session → user mapping
+│   └── schema.ts                 # Stored-record Zod schemas
+└── lib/
+    ├── logger.ts                 # Structured JSON, PII-redacting          [chunk 1]
+    ├── result.ts                 # Result<T, E>                            [chunk 1]
+    └── time.ts                   # Clock seam for tests
+```
+
+## OAuth sequence (two-legged)
+
+```mermaid
+sequenceDiagram
+    actor U as User
+    participant C as MCP Client
+    participant W as MCP Worker
+    participant MO as MCP OAuth
+    participant D as Discord OAuth
+    participant UDO as UserTokenDO
+    participant SDO as SessionDO
+
+    Note over C,W: Phase 1 — Registration
+    C->>W: GET /.well-known/oauth-authorization-server
+    W-->>C: OAuth 2.1 metadata (PKCE required)
+    C->>MO: POST /register (DCR, RFC 7591)
+    MO-->>C: {client_id, client_secret}
+
+    Note over U,D: Phase 2 — Authorization (two legs)
+    C->>MO: GET /authorize?client_id=...&code_challenge=...&state=S1
+    MO->>W: render consent ("Connect Discord")
+    U->>W: Authorize
+    W->>D: 302 /oauth2/authorize?scope=identify+guilds&state=S2&code_challenge=...
+    U->>D: Login + approve
+    D-->>W: 302 /discord/callback?code=DC&state=S2
+    W->>D: POST /oauth2/token (code + PKCE verifier)
+    D-->>W: {access_token, refresh_token, expires_in}
+    W->>D: GET /users/@me
+    D-->>W: {id=U123, username}
+    W->>UDO: put(U123, {tokens, expires_at})
+    W->>MO: mint MCP auth code MC, bind MC↔U123
+    MO-->>C: 302 redirect_uri?code=MC&state=S1
+
+    Note over C,W: Phase 3 — Token exchange
+    C->>MO: POST /token (code=MC, PKCE verifier)
+    MO->>SDO: create session SID, bind SID↔U123
+    MO-->>C: {access_token=SID, token_type=Bearer}
+
+    Note over C,W: Phase 4 — Tool call
+    C->>W: POST /mcp (Authorization: Bearer SID, Mcp-Session-Id: SID)
+    W->>SDO: lookup(SID) → U123
+    W->>UDO: getValidToken(U123)
+    alt expires_at - now < 60s
+        UDO->>D: POST /oauth2/token (refresh_token)
+        D-->>UDO: {new access, new refresh, expires_in}
+        UDO->>UDO: atomic put (rotation)
+    end
+    UDO-->>W: access_token
+    W->>W: authz guard (guild membership)
+    W->>D: Data-plane call with `Bot ${BOT_TOKEN}`
+    D-->>W: response
+    W-->>C: MCP result { content: [...] }
+```
+
+Key invariant: the user's access token is only used for **identity +
+authorization** (`/users/@me`, `/users/@me/guilds`). Data-plane calls
+(send/read messages, reactions, threads) use the **bot token**. The MCP
+client never sees a Discord token.
+
+## Build plan — chunks
+
+Each chunk must build, typecheck, pass tests, and lint independently. Each
+chunk is exported as a `git format-patch` to
+`wol-sok-mono/patches/discord-mcp-oauth/chunk-<N>/` for manual replay (see
+sandbox note below).
+
+- [x] **Chunk 1 — Scaffold + foundations.** TS strict, Vitest (node pool),
+      ESLint, Prettier, `wrangler.toml` with DO bindings, `.dev.vars.example`;
+      `src/env.ts`, `src/lib/logger.ts`, `src/lib/result.ts`. 24 passing tests.
+- [ ] **Chunk 2 — Discord REST client.** `discord/errors.ts` (typed
+      hierarchy), `discord/rate-limiter.ts` (X-RateLimit-\* + Retry-After),
+      `discord/rest-client.ts` (typed fetch wrapper), `discord/schemas.ts`
+      (Zod for the payloads this project touches). Unit tests with `fetch` mocks
+      covering happy path, 429 backoff, 403/404 mapping, and schema drift.
+- [ ] **Chunk 3 — OAuth + storage.** `storage/user-token-do.ts` (atomic
+      rotation), `storage/session-do.ts`, `oauth/discord-client.ts` (PKCE,
+      exchange, refresh), `oauth/mcp-provider.ts`, `oauth/bridge.ts`. Vitest
+      Workers pool added here for DO tests. Test: OAuth happy path, refresh
+      rotation, concurrent-refresh serialization.
+- [ ] **Chunk 4 — MCP server + tools.** `mcp/server.ts`, `mcp/transport.ts`,
+      `authz/guild-membership.ts`, and the eight tools under `tools/` with
+      one-happy + one-error test each.
+- [ ] **Chunk 5 — Entry point + docs.** `src/index.ts` (Hono router wiring
+      all the above), `README.md` (quickstart + client setup), `ARCHITECTURE.md`
+      (this plan's successor as the shipping doc), `docs/clients.md`,
+      `docs/admin.md` (bot invite + permissions), GitHub Actions CI workflow,
+      badges.
+
+## Delivery mechanism
+
+Sandbox outbound git is restricted to `wolfsoko/wol-sok-mono`. The project
+itself lives at `wolfsoko/discord-mcp-oauth`. Workflow:
+
+1. Claude commits chunks locally in the sandbox at `/root/repos/discord-mcp-oauth`.
+2. Each chunk is exported via `git format-patch` to
+   `wol-sok-mono/patches/discord-mcp-oauth/chunk-<N>/`.
+3. The patch is committed on `claude/discord-mcp-oauth-FO3GL` and pushed to
+   `wol-sok-mono`.
+4. The maintainer applies the patch locally in the target repo and pushes.
+
+Apply instructions: `patches/discord-mcp-oauth/README.md` in `wol-sok-mono`.
+
+## Open items / deferred decisions
+
+- **Commit signing.** Disabled locally in the sandbox clone (`git config
+commit.gpgsign false`) because the sandbox signing infra isn't aware of
+  this repo. When the patch is replayed locally, the maintainer's own
+  signing kicks in.
+- **Compat date drift.** `wrangler.toml` targets `2026-04-01`. Local
+  `workerd` only supports up to `2025-10-11` today and warns; it's a
+  local-dev-only gap and will resolve when Miniflare/workerd updates.
+- **Claude.ai vs. Claude Code vs. mcp-remote callback shapes.** Covered by
+  DCR in principle; chunk 4 adds an integration test matrix to catch
+  regressions.
+- **Forum post CRUD.** Stretch goal, not in MVP.
